solutions.content:
**Complexity**
- time: O(n^2)
- space: O(n)

**Implementation**
```
public class Solution {
    public int NumTrees(int n) {

        if(n <= 1)
            return 1;

        // dp[i]: # of unique BST formed by i nodes
        int[] dp = new int[n+1];
        dp[0] = 1;
        dp[1] = 1;

        // build dp array for 2 nodes, 3 nodes, ..., n nodes
        for(int i = 2; i <= n; i++)
        {
            // there j number of nodes in the left subtree
            for(int j = 0; j < i; j++)
            {
				// number of BST constructed by i nodes = # of left sub-BST * # of righ sub-BST
                dp[i] += dp[j] * dp[i-1-j];
            }
        }

        return dp[n];
    }
}
```

