We can solve the problem using dynamic programming. We will solve for small problem (i<n) then will use this results to find for other. 

For n=1, dp[n]=1, since 1 BST can be formed with this.
For n=2, dp[n]=2, since 2 BST can be formed with this.
For n=3, there would be 5 BST as desribed below:

No of BST in which there are 0 left children and 2 right children (dp[0] * dp[2])
No of BST in which there are 1 left children and 1 right children (dp[1] * dp[1])
No of BST in which  there are 2 left children and 0 right children (dp[2] * dp[0])

Total number of BST =2+1+2=5.
