Discrete Mathematics by Richard Johnsonbaugh (7th edition)
Page 491
Theorem 9.8.12: "There are Cn nonisomorphic binary trees with n vertices where Cn = C(2n, n)/(n+1) is the nth Catalan number."

```
public int numTrees(int n) {
	//formula is C(2n,n)/(n+1)
	double answer = 1;
	for(double i = n+2; i<=2*n; i++) {
		answer*=i;
		answer/=i-n;
	}
	return (int)Math.round(answer);
}
```
O(n) time
O(1) memory

